==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[δαίμων]]''' (''daemon'') " a god, goddess, divine power, genius, guardian spirit", from '''[[δαίω]]''' (''daio'') "to divide, to distribute destinies, to allot".

===Alternative spellings===
*[[dæmon]]

===Noun===
'''daemon''' (''plural'' '''daemons''')

#(''Commonwealth English'') An older spelling of [[demon]].
#(''Greek mythology'') A [[deity]].
# {{cattag|Computing}}: A [[program]] running as a [[background process]], performing tasks such as serving files to remote clients.

